{'push_id': 9702006914, 'size': 1, 'distinct_size': 1, 'ref': 'refs/heads/captioning_sample', 'head': '9c7944159740d56270db8c574eec08b8a814b4c6', 'before': '15571a5db8a351f2638a8d4a5eccac9ec4b28acf', 'commits': [{'sha': '9c7944159740d56270db8c574eec08b8a814b4c6', 'author': {'email': '30323598+v-jaswel@users.noreply.github.com', 'name': 'Jason Wells'}, 'message': 'Update caption.py

- TrueText is always on.
- The command line argument for stable partial result threshold is now -t instead of -r.
- Compressed audio format is now supported.
- As a result, gstreamer is now required.
- A new command line argument, -c, specifies compressed audio format. Default is ANY.
- Audio input file, if any, is assumed to be local, not remote.
- If audio input file name has extension .wav, it is assumed to be uncompressed audio; otherwise, it is assumed to be compressed audio.
- Pull stream is used for both uncompressed (.wav) and compressed audio formats.', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure-Samples/cognitive-services-speech-sdk/commits/9c7944159740d56270db8c574eec08b8a814b4c6'}]}

Tried to call Helper.OpenWavFile() with a .wav file that contained a LIST chunk before the data chunk. As a result, I failed the assertion "Wrong data tag in wav."

Added code to detect and dispose of LIST chunk. Tested successfully on .wav file with and without LIST chunk.

Screenshot of hex editor showing LIST chunk:
https://imgur.com/eU05hAA

More info:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/63929283/what-is-a-list-chunk-in-a-riff-wav-header
https://www.recordingblogs.com/wiki/list-chunk-of-a-wave-file

- Removed -a flag. Per Darren Cohen, prioritizing accuracy over low latency for language identification + continuous recognition is not supported.
- Added -u flag to handle recognizing event instead of recognized.
- Only use v2 endpoint when language identification is enabled.
- Added note: The Speech SDK on Windows requires the Microsoft Visual C++ Redistributable for Visual Studio 2019 on the system.
- Replaced property name strings with PropertyId enum values.
- Replaced "endpoint" with "region" in usage string.
- Replaced snake casing with pascal casing for classes and methods, camel casing for values.', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/v-jaswel/cognitive-services-speech-sdk/commits/ef81c7f1745291b9183e46305d7872a0d93f2e9f'}]}
